      "name": "Monte Carlo hemolysis index sweep — 5 operating points",
      "description": "ValidationResult for predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) across five flow-speed combinations using Monte Carlo UQ. Predicted NIH values fall below the absolute clinical threshold at all operating points with 95% confidence. This result was generated under solver configuration ansys-cfx-hemolysis-2026-q1-build-7-rc2. The assessment team notes that the release candidate and the released solver build differ only by a single patch applied to the turbulence-wall treatment module; internal testing of a single benchmark case showed no change in NIH to four significant figures, and on that basis the result is carried forward without re-execution under the released build.",
